Let me start my review with the good sides of the great game under the name Counter Strike: Global Offensive.
So the first good point about this game that I have found is the fact that you can get free money via in-game drops;
The second good thing about this game is, I forgor 💀. With good sides of CS:GO out of the way I shall begin to describe how inadequate this game is for being a competitive First Person Shooter and how atrocious the experience is. I would like to state that I will not mention the fact that players from some regions are hopelessly amateurish in terms of cooperation and in-game skill nor will I be mentioning how many acts of grooming underage women have I done. The gameplay itself is borderline acceptable although 64 tick servers on which competitive games are running on aren't, because of servers having a tickrate lower than IQ of an average Equatorial Guinea citizen you wouldnt be able to accurately hit your shots, not because of your "bad spray control" but rather the fact that if you're playing on servers that literal Somalian pirates have been setting up, your shots can be registered to have landed in a different place than from a client side, which is also a problem on higher tickrates. The game often ignores the limits that you have set up in the settings menu and will put in a Indian server even though you're from Brazil, hence there are people with ping values that exceed 300 which is almost a number of children in my basement. The anticheat and trust factor in this game are as a matter of fact a funny joke although I would like to see their actual addition to the game. On the ending note I would like to state that I am not a pedophile, I do not groom underage girls nor do I capture children, I also have no idea how did the tapes with child porn on them appear in my closet. I do not believe in god but everyday I pray for my anime waifu (and now since there is like this whole war thing going on; Ukraine). Glory to China!
